doctype html
html
  head
    title ZAS Timestamp
    link(rel='shortcut icon', href='data:image/x-icon;base64,', type='image/x-icon')
    link(href='https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Roboto', rel='stylesheet', type='text/css')
    link(href='/public/main.css', rel='stylesheet', type='text/css')
  body
    .container
      h1 A time stamp microservice
      h3 Part 1 of Free Code Camp Backend Challenges
    .explanation
      h4 What can you do with this microservice?
      ul
        li You can pass a string as a parameter and if it contains a unix timestamp or a natural language date (example: January 1, 2016)
          ol
            li It returns both the Unix timestamp and the natural language form of that date.
            li If it does not contain a date or Unix timestamp, it returns null for those properties.
        li
          h3 Example Input
          ul
            li
              code  #{title}December%2015,%202015
            li
              code  #{title}1450137600
            li
              code  #{title}December 15, 2015
            li
              code  #{title}December 15 2015
            li
              code  #{title}December152015
        li
          h3 Example Output
          code { "unix": 1450137600, "natural": "December 15, 2015" }